      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.10</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.11</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>地無以寧將恐發，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>If earth were not thus sure, 'twould break and bend;</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-039__align-008">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-039</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">3</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.11 - 老子 39.12</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.12 - 老子 39.14</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>神無以靈將恐歇，谷無以盈將恐竭，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Without these powers, the spirits soon would fail; If not so filled, the drought would parch each vale; Without that life, creatures would pass away;</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-039__align-009">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-039</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.13</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.15 - 老子 39.16</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>萬物無以生將恐滅，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Princes and kings, without that moral sway, However grand and high, would all decay.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-039__align-010">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-039</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.14 - 老子 39.15</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.17</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>侯王無以貴高將恐蹶。故貴以賤為本，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Thus it is that dignity finds its (firm) root in its (previous) meanness, and what is lofty finds its stability in the lowness (from which it rises).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-039__align-011">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-039</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">3</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.16 - 老子 39.18</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.18</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>高以下為基。是以侯王自稱孤﹑寡﹑不穀。此非以賤為本邪？</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Hence princes and kings call themselves 'Orphans,' 'Men of small virtue,' and as 'Carriages without a nave.' Is not this an acknowledgment that in their considering themselves mean they see the foundation of their dignity?</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-039__align-012">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-039</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 39.19 - 老子 39.20</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 39.19</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>非乎？故致數輿無輿，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>So it is that in the enumeration of the different parts of a carriage we do not come on what makes it answer the ends of a carriage.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
